================================================================================
FOLDER STRUCTURE  (www/csrs/)
================================================================================

  CSRS.py                  — The main daemon script. Runs in the background,
                             scrapes match results, calculates Elo ratings, and
                             writes the encoded data.save file. You generally do
                             not need to edit this unless you are changing the
                             rating formula or scraping logic.

  data.save                — Binary-encoded snapshot of all rating data. It is
                             base64 + zlib + JSON. Do NOT edit this by hand.
                             It is regenerated by the daemon on every run.

  README.txt               — Original project notes.

  srvr.info                — This file. Documents the server setup and all
                             changes made on the zerxio branch.

  csrs_api/                — Everything the web server actually runs.
    main.py                — FastAPI backend. Reads data.save and serves all
                             API endpoints. This is the file most changed on
                             the zerxio branch. See section below.
    frontend/
      index.html           — The CSRS web dashboard. Single-page app with a
                             sidebar, rankings table, match history, simulation,
                             elite-over-time chart, and head-to-head view.
                             Also heavily changed on zerxio. See section below.
    Dockerfile             — Builds the csrs-web container (FastAPI + frontend).
    Dockerfile.daemon      — Builds the csrs-daemon container (CSRS.py runner).
    docker-compose.yml     — Standalone compose file for the csrs services alone
                             (not used in production; production uses
                             /home/laperic/docker/ntfy/docker-compose.yml).
    requirements.txt       — Python deps for the web API (fastapi, uvicorn, etc.)
    requirements.daemon.txt — Python deps for the daemon (playwright, etc.)
    gitignore              — Ignores __pycache__, .env, etc.

================================================================================
HOW THE SYSTEM WORKS END TO END
================================================================================

1. git-sync-dev container polls GitHub every 60s for the zerxio branch and
   writes it to /home/laperic/git-sync-root-dev/current/ on the host.

2. csrs-web-dev container mounts that path read-only as /data-dev/.
   It runs: uvicorn main:app --app-dir /data-dev/current/www/csrs/csrs_api
   So when git-sync-dev pulls a new commit, the running code updates on the
   next container restart (or srvr reload).

3. Caddy routes:
   - dev.saloraxz.com  →  csrs-web-dev:8000   (full interactive dashboard)
   - raw.saloraxz.com  →  csrs-web-dev:8000   (rewritten to /api/raw.txt)

4. csrs-daemon runs CSRS.py which writes data.save. csrs-web-dev reads it.

================================================================================
main.py — WHAT EACH SECTION DOES
================================================================================

CONFIG (top of file)
  DATA_FILE       Path to data.save (set by env CSRS_DATA_FILE)
  FRONTEND_DIR    Path to the frontend folder (set by env CSRS_FRONTEND_DIR)
  SOURCE_REF      Set to "zerxio" by the docker-compose env so the raw page
                  can display which branch is serving the data.

ELO CONSTANTS
  RATING_CAP, RATING_FLOOR, K_WIN, K_LOSS, PROVISIONAL_*, DIMINISHING_*,
  MISMATCH_*, PITY_*, ELITE_THRESHOLD, TIERS, MAPS, ENVS
  — These are exact copies of the DEFAULT_CONFIG values from CSRS.py.
    They must stay in sync with that file or simulation results will differ
    from what the daemon actually calculated.

load_data()
  Reads data.save, base64-decodes it, decompresses with zlib, returns a dict
  with keys: teams, history, peaks, provisional_teams, aliases.

_calculate_points()
  Full port of CSRS.py calculate_points(). Used only in simulate_elo().
  Takes two team ratings, a result, map diff, tier, env, and modifiers.
  Returns the new rating for one team after one match.

_build_match_date_index() / _get_last_match_date()
  Build a sorted index of match dates per team so depreciation can be
  calculated in O(log n) instead of scanning all history every time.

_calculate_depreciation() / _apply_depreciation()
  Mirrors CSRS.py depreciation logic. Ratings decay after 14 days of
  inactivity. Used on every ranking/team display so scores reflect
  real standing, not just raw stored value.

_calculate_form_at_match_index()
  Calculates a team's form score (0–100) using the last 15 matches before
  a given index. Weighted by recency, win rate, map rate, and competition
  level. Used in simulation to adjust expected win probability.

simulate_elo()
  Full match simulator. Given two team names and match parameters (tier, env,
  bo, grand_final), returns win probabilities and all possible scoreline
  deltas. Accounts for provisional status and depreciation.

--- API ENDPOINTS ---

GET /api/rankings
  Returns all teams sorted by depreciated Elo. Each entry includes rank,
  points, raw_points, depreciation_loss, peak, days_inactive, and sparkline
  (last 30 days of match results). Supports ?limit= and ?search=.

GET /api/team/{team_name}
  Full detail for one team: current rank, rating, record, peak, and
  a chronological timeline of every match they played with deltas.

GET /api/history
  Paginated match history, newest first. Filterable by ?team=, ?tier=, ?event=.

POST /api/simulate
  Accepts { team1, team2, tier, env, bo, grand_final } and returns win
  probability and point deltas for every possible scoreline.

GET /api/analytics/summary
  Aggregate stats: tier/env breakdown, top events by match count, team winrates.

GET /api/analytics/h2h
  Head-to-head record between two teams. Requires ?team1=&team2=.

GET /api/analytics/elite-over-time
  Time series of daily Elo for all teams that reached the elite threshold
  (850 pts) in a given date range. Used by the Elite Teams Over Time chart.
  Accepts ?start_date=, ?end_date=.

GET /api/teams
  Simple list of all team names. Supports ?search=.

GET /api/meta
  Returns version, total_teams, total_matches, last_match date.

GET /health
  Returns {"status": "ok"}. Used by the container health check.

--- RAW DATA ENDPOINTS (added on zerxio, June 20 2026) ---

GET /api/raw.txt                          (plain text — used by raw.saloraxz.com)
  Human-readable text dump of CSRS data. Sections:
    - Top N rankings
    - Recent M matches
    - Elo per day (last N days, top K teams each day)
    - On this day rankings (same month/day across past years)
  Query params:
    limit=25          number of teams in rankings section
    matches=20        number of recent matches shown
    daily_days=14     how many days back the Elo-per-day section covers
    daily_teams=5     teams shown per day in the Elo-per-day section
    on_this_day_limit=5  teams shown per historical snapshot
    month=            override the month for on-this-day (1–12, default=today)
    day=              override the day for on-this-day (1–31, default=today)

  Examples:
    http://raw.saloraxz.com
    http://raw.saloraxz.com?month=3&day=10&on_this_day_limit=10
    http://raw.saloraxz.com?daily_days=30&daily_teams=10

GET /api/raw/elo-per-day                  (JSON)
  Returns end-of-day Elo snapshots. Each entry has date, matches played that
  day, and a ranked list of top teams with their points at day close.
  Query params:
    days=30     how many days back (max 3650)
    teams=10    teams per day snapshot (max 100)

GET /api/raw/on-this-day                  (JSON)
  Returns historical ranking snapshots for the same month/day across all
  years that had match data. Useful for "on this day in 2025, rankings were…"
  Query params:
    month=   month number (default=today)
    day=     day number (default=today)
    limit=10 teams per snapshot

--- HELPER FUNCTIONS (added for raw data, June 20 2026) ---

_parse_match_datetime(date_str)
  Parses CSRS date strings ("YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM UTC") into datetime objects.
  Handles both full timestamps and date-only strings.

_build_daily_rating_snapshots(history)
  Walks all match history in chronological order and builds a dict of
  end-of-day Elo snapshots: {"YYYY-MM-DD": {team_name: pts_after}}.
  Also returns a count of matches per day. Used by all three raw endpoints.

_top_rankings_for_snapshot(points_by_team, limit)
  Takes a day's snapshot dict and returns a sorted ranked list up to limit.

================================================================================
frontend/index.html — WHAT EACH SECTION DOES
================================================================================

This is a single HTML file with embedded CSS and JS. No build step needed.
It fetches all data from the API at /api/* on the same origin.

SIDEBAR
  Navigation links for: Rankings, Match History, Simulate, Team Analytics
  (Elite Teams Over Time is the one working sub-page; the others are WIP),
  and Head to Head. Clicking a link swaps the active .page div.
  Sidebar footer shows total_teams, total_matches, last match date, version.

RANKINGS PAGE
  Loads /api/rankings?limit=200. Renders a sortable table with rank, team
  name, points, peak, peak rank, and a sparkline (30-day trend SVG).
  Typing in the search box filters client-side without re-fetching.
  Clicking a team name opens the Team Detail panel.

MATCH HISTORY PAGE
  Loads /api/history (paginated, 30 per page). Filters by team, tier, event.
  Shows date, event, tier badge, score, and winner.

TEAM DETAIL PANEL (overlay, not a separate page)
  Opens when you click any team name. Fetches /api/team/{name}.
  Shows: current rating, global rank, W/L record, peak rating.
  Below the stats: a Chart.js line chart of rating over time, then a
  full match history table for that team with per-match deltas.

SIMULATE PAGE
  Inputs for team1, team2, tier, env, bo, grand_final checkbox.
  POSTs to /api/simulate and renders a scoreline table with win % and deltas.
  Both teams' current ratings, depreciation, and form adjustment are shown.

ELITE TEAMS OVER TIME PAGE
  Date range pickers (start/end). Fetches /api/analytics/elite-over-time.
  Renders a Chart.js multi-line chart — one line per team that exceeded 850
  Elo in the selected range. Below the chart is a colour-coded legend with
  each team's peak, final rating, and diff over the range.

HEAD TO HEAD PAGE
  Two team name inputs. Fetches /api/analytics/h2h.
  Shows overall win counts and a match-by-match history table.

